refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 public ZMQSocketZMQContext::getSocket
 inttype
 stringpersistent_id&null;
 callableon_new_socket&null;



 Shortcut for creating new sockets from the context. If the context is not persistent the persistent_id 
 parameter is ignored and the socket falls back to being non-persistent. The on_new_socket is called only
 when a new underlying socket structure is created.

 &reftitle.examples;



    A ZMQContext example


     Basic usage



<?php
/* Allocate a new context */
$context = new ZMQContext();

/* Create a new socket */
$socket = $context->getSocket(ZMQ::SOCKET_REQ, 'my sock');

/* Connect the socket */
$socket->connect("tcp://example.com:1234");

/* Send a request */
$socket->send("Hello there");

/* Receive back the response */
$message = $socket->recv();
echo "Received message: {$message}\n";
?>
